# Warmth UI Standard — Warm Liquid Glass

All user-facing UI (web `web/`, iOS, watchOS) uses a warm glassmorphism,
iOS-26 "liquid glass" aesthetic: frosted translucent surfaces over a warm
white background, with high-contrast black text and red/orange accents.

## Color tokens (warm)

Use these everywhere (web Tailwind + iOS/watchOS Swift `Color(hex:)`):

| Token | Hex | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|
| Red brand | `#dc2626` | ICP hot, passive audio, strong connections |
| Ember (dark orange) | `#c2410c` | primary actions, "hottest" |
| Flame (deep orange) | `#ea580c` | accents, links, ICP warm |
| Orange | `#f97316` | brand accent, toggles |
| Orange light | `#fb923c` | hover/active text |
| Amber | `#f59e0b` | status pending |
| Warm stone | `#a8a29e` | ICP cold / low interest |
| Ink 900–600 | `#160d07`→`#3a2615` | body text, headings |
| Surface | `#ffffff` / `#fff8f3` | page + glass base |

ICP heat ramp: **hot = red `#dc2626`**, **warm = orange `#ea580c`**,
**cold = stone `#a8a29e`**. Background = warm orange/red radial blobs over
white (see `web/src/index.css`). Text defaults to **ink-900** (near-black).

## Typography

**Space Grotesk** is the brand font everywhere.
- Web: self-hosted at `web/public/fonts/SpaceGrotesk-VariableFont_wght.ttf`
  (`@font-face` in `index.css`, set as Tailwind `fontFamily.sans`).
- iOS/watchOS: add the same `.ttf` to the app bundle + Info.plist
  `UIAppFonts`, use `Font.custom("Space Grotesk", size:)`.

## How to apply (web/)

Use the shared utilities/components, don't re-invent:

- `.glass` / `.glass-strong` — frosted surface (`web/src/index.css`)
- `.glass-interactive` — hover lift; `.glass-pill` — chips/badges
- Components: `GlassCard`, `GlassPanel`, `ICPBadge`, `SignalChip`, `Toggle`,
  `MetDetailDrawer`, `Avatar`, `CompanyLogo`, `Toast`, `Logos` in `web/src/components/`

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — warm frosted, high-contrast black text
<GlassCard className="p-5"><h3 className="font-semibold text-ink-900">Lead Inbox</h3></GlassCard>

// ❌ BAD — flat opaque, cool grays, no blur
<div className="rounded bg-gray-800 p-5 text-gray-400">…</div>
```

## Don'ts

- No flat opaque cards or cool grays/blues/purples for primary surfaces.
- No charts/graphs on the main dashboard canvas.
- Don't drop contrast for "subtle glass" — keep text legible in bright venues.
